(8015, 420, 'modules_6_description', 'Studies have shown that over the ten year period ending in 2018, approximately 59% of the United States population has been a victim of medical data breach due to a hack of a facility where the victim was treated. Hacking has been identified as the leading cause of healthcare data breaches. Because of this, it is imperative for healthcare facilities to stay vigilant against cyber attacks.\r\n\r\nAlso dangerous to busy medical practices are technology outages caused by a disaster, whether natural or man-made. IT companies such as Dwyer IT are able to put disaster recovery plans in place to ensure that a medical office is up and running with minimal downtime; this will improve office efficiency, patient treatment and ensure peace of mind.For a busy medical practice, it is difficult, if not impossible, to handle all IT-related functions alone; a doctor\'s valuable time is much better served treating patients. The managed IT professionals at Dwyer IT are HIPAA experts; we offer a wide array of IT services that maximize efficiency, minimize cost and assure compliance.'),
